{
  "texts": [
    "Recent advancements explored the incorporation of knowledge bases into LLMs, enabling models to access structured information during the generation process [20].",
    "The integration of knowledge graphs allowed for better context understanding and factual consistency, as LLMs could reference verified data points [21].",
    "Hybrid models combining statistical and rule-based approaches were implemented to enhance factual accuracy, as they leveraged the strengths of both paradigms, using statistical methods for natural language understanding and rule-based systems for ensuring factual correctness [22,23].",
    "Efforts were also made to improve the internal architecture of LLMs, such as introducing attention mechanisms specifically designed to focus on verifiable content, by guiding LLMs' attention towards credible information [24].",
    "Additionally, adversarial training techniques were employed to expose and correct factual inaccuracies, resulting in more robust models [25]."
  ]
}